  "text": "[22] Such equatorial zonal jets at AAIW level have also been diagnosed recently by high resolution primitive equation numerical models. [CITATION_1] obtain alternating zonal jets, between 12°S and 5°N, agreeing latitudinally with our observations but with velocities (averaged over 10 years) much weaker (order of 1 cm s À1 ). In the equatorial Pacific, [CITATION_2] also find alternating zonal jets (after a 5-year averaging) with similar latitudinal widths and weak zonal velocities. ",
